The paper proposes a formal definition of the value alignment problem in autonomous systems, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on the interaction between a human and a robot, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of AI, robotics, and human-computer interaction. The paper also introduces a cooperative, partial-information game with two agents, which implies that it could be categorized under reinforcement learning and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.HC, followed by cs.LG and cs.SY.
